<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 16 at 4:28AM CDT until April 16 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 500 AM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN MADISON AND CENTRAL CARROLL COUNTIES...
At 428 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Clifty, moving
east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations in or near the path include...
Berryville...                     Green Forest...
Rudd...                           Urbanette...
Rule...                           Clifty...
Forum...                          Rockhouse...
Cabanal...                        Metalton...
Connor...                         Best...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
